data.content:
The root cause is that **Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi 10.0** upgraded from **OpenAPI.NET v1** to **OpenAPI.NET v2**, which has several breaking changes. Here's what changed and the fixes:

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` removed
The `IOpenApiAny` type hierarchy is gone. `Schema.Example` is now `JsonNode?`.

### 2. `OpenApiSecurityScheme` with `Reference` → `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`
Model objects no longer carry a `Reference` property. Dedicated reference types exist in `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References`.

### 3. `Schema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI 3.1 (which v2 targets) expresses nullability via the `Type` flags enum (`JsonSchemaType`), not a separate `Nullable` bool.

---

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;          // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References; // for OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // OpenApiString → JsonValue
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // Reference-wrapper type replaces OpenApiSecurityScheme + OpenApiReference
    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
            {
                // Nullable bool → clear the Null flag from the Type enum
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

| .NET 9 (OpenAPI.NET v1) | .NET 10 (OpenAPI.NET v2) |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| `new OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ..., Id = "oauth2" } }` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")` |
| `property.Value.Nullable = false` | `property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
